# Release + publish — agent checklist

> **Trigger:** version bump, `git tag`, npm publish, GitHub Release, `release.yml`, CHANGELOG, npm README.

## Non-negotiable order

1. `pnpm verify` green on `developing`
2. PR `developing` → `main` (CI `test` + approval)
3. **Bump version** in **all six** publishable packages (same semver)
4. **CHANGELOG** — move `[Unreleased]` → `[X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD`
5. **npm-facing docs** — update READMEs (see checklist below) **before** tag
6. Commit + merge to `main`
7. **Only then** create and push git tag `vX.Y.Z`
8. Release workflow publishes npm + GitHub Release
9. Sync `developing` from `main`

**NEVER** push a tag before steps 3–6. **NEVER** run `pnpm publish` locally — CI-only (`scripts/assert-ci-publish.mjs`).

## npm-facing documentation (MANDATORY before tag)

npm renders each package's `README.md` from the repo. Stale **Current release** text (e.g. still **v1.7.0** after bumping to **1.8.0**) ships to [npmjs.com](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@br-validators/core) on publish.

### Files to update every release

| File | What to sync |
|------|----------------|
| `packages/br-validators/README.md` | `## Current release`, version table, document-type table, reference-data table, feature bullets |
| `README.md` (repo root) | `## Current release` version table + release blurb |
| `apps/cli/README.md` | Core version in intro line |
| `packages/br-validators-zod/README.md` | Core version in intro line |
| `packages/br-validators-rhf/README.md` | Core version in intro line |
| `packages/br-validators-express/README.md` | Core version in intro line |
| `packages/br-validators-vue/README.md` | Core version in intro line |

### Pre-tag audit (run after bump, before `git tag`)

```bash
VERSION="1.8.0"   # planned release — no v prefix
PREV="1.7.0"      # last published — adjust per release

# 1. No stale previous version in publishable READMEs
if rg -n "$PREV" README.md packages/br-validators/README.md apps/cli/README.md \
  packages/br-validators-*/README.md 2>/dev/null; then
  echo "FAIL: stale $PREV in README"; exit 1
fi

# 2. New version present in all seven READMEs
for F in README.md packages/br-validators/README.md apps/cli/README.md \
  packages/br-validators-zod/README.md packages/br-validators-rhf/README.md \
  packages/br-validators-express/README.md packages/br-validators-vue/README.md; do
  rg -q "$VERSION" "$F" || { echo "MISSING $VERSION in $F"; exit 1; }
done

# 3. CHANGELOG section exists for this version
rg -q "## \[$VERSION\]" CHANGELOG.md || { echo "CHANGELOG missing [$VERSION]"; exit 1; }

echo "README audit OK"
```

### Content checklist (new subpaths / features)

When the release adds validators or reference data:

- [ ] `packages/br-validators/README.md` — **All supported types** table (document + platform rows)
- [ ] `packages/br-validators/README.md` — **Reference data** table (if applicable)
- [ ] `CHANGELOG.md` — `[Unreleased]` moved to dated `## [X.Y.Z]`
- [ ] Root `README.md` — **Current release** blurb matches CHANGELOG scope (not previous release highlights)

**Post-publish verify:** `npm view @br-validators/core version` and spot-check https://www.npmjs.com/package/@br-validators/core README.

## Files that MUST match

| File | Field |
|------|--------|
| `packages/br-validators/package.json` | `"version"` |
| `apps/cli/package.json` | `"version"` |
| `packages/br-validators-zod/package.json` | `"version"` |
| `packages/br-validators-rhf/package.json` | `"version"` |
| `packages/br-validators-express/package.json` | `"version"` |
| `packages/br-validators-vue/package.json` | `"version"` |
| Git tag | `v` + same semver (e.g. `v1.6.1`) |

## Pre-tag verification (run before `git tag`)

```bash
VERSION="1.6.1"   # planned release — no v prefix
for PKG in packages/br-validators apps/cli packages/br-validators-zod packages/br-validators-rhf packages/br-validators-express packages/br-validators-vue; do
  V=$(jq -r .version "$PKG/package.json")
  test "$VERSION" = "$V" || { echo "MISMATCH $PKG=$V"; exit 1; }
done
echo "OK"
git tag -l "v$VERSION"     # must be empty before new tag
```

## Tag + publish (automated — CI only)

```bash
git checkout main && git pull
git tag -a v1.6.1 -m "Release v1.6.1"
git push origin v1.6.1
```

Workflow: `.github/workflows/release.yml` — requires secret **`NPM_TOKEN`**. Publishes all six packages; sets npm **`latest`**.

**Re-run:** Actions → Release → workflow_dispatch with tag `v1.6.1`.

## Common mistakes

| Mistake | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Tag `v1.6.1` but `package.json` still `1.6.0` | Bump all six `package.json`, merge `main`, delete bad tag, retag |
| Tag on wrong commit (old code) | Delete remote tag + release; tag `main` HEAD after merge |
| Local `pnpm publish` | Blocked by design — push tag or re-run Release workflow |
| Re-tag same version already on npm | Bump to next patch/prerelease — or re-run workflow (skips existing versions) |
| Any package version differs | Set all six to identical semver before tag |
| `express` / `vue` 404 on npm | Fix `NPM_TOKEN` — token must allow **create** on `@br-validators/*` |

## Agent duties on release tasks

1. Bump **all six** `package.json` files in the same commit.
2. Update `CHANGELOG.md` for the release scope only.
3. **Audit and update all seven npm-facing READMEs** (see npm-facing documentation above).
4. Run pre-tag verification commands; report mismatch before tagging.
5. Do **not** paste or commit `NPM_TOKEN` — GitHub secret only.
6. After release, confirm: `npm view @br-validators/core version` (and express, vue); spot-check npm README.

**Docs:** `docs/BRANCHING.md`, `docs/VERSIONING.md` — **Troubleshooting:** `npm-publish-ci.mdc`
